Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the
boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@olive oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Put a large #frying pan{} on high heat with a drizzle of @olive oil{}.

Once hot, add the @chicken breast{260%g}(diced) and fry until browned all
over, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

Add the @chorizo{90%g}(sliced) and sweetcorn. Fry, stirring occasionally, until
starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes} more.

Once browned, lower the heat to medium.

Add the shallot to the pan. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @baby spinach{40%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the spinach has wilted, add the @creme fraiche{100%g} and
@water{50%ml}(for the sauce) to the pan.

Bring to the boil, stirring, then remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Mix in half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Season to taste with
@ground black pepper{} and @salt{}.

Add the cooked pasta to the sauce and gently mix until well coated, reheating
quickly if necessary.

Serve your chorizo and sweetcorn pasta in large #bowls{} with the remaining
cheese sprinkled on top to finish.

Enjoy!